<!--
A self-evolving agent whose only memory is a blob store it reads and writes
across turns. Run it through the one binary:

    beet --main=examples/thread/self_evolving.bsx

`{FsStore}` mounts the store on the thread (an ancestor the `<StoreToolset/>`
resolves), the agent evolves `notes.md` over ten turns (`{RepeatTimes}`), and
`{RunThread}` exits when they complete. The transcript renders inline.
-->
<div>
	<div {RepeatTimes{total_times:10}} {RunThread}>
		<div {Thread} {Sequence} {FsStore{path:"target/examples/self_evolving"}} bx:ref="thread">
			<CreateActor name="System" kind="System">
				<CreatePost text="
You are a self-evolving agent whose only memory is a persistent blob store.
Each turn, evolve your own knowledge base in small, concrete steps:

1. Call list-blobs to see what you have stored.
2. If `notes.md` does not exist, create it with write-blob holding a short list
   of three things you would like to learn or improve about yourself.
3. Otherwise read-blob `notes.md`, then use edit-text to refine exactly one
   entry: mark it done, or replace it with a more specific follow-up goal.

Keep `notes.md` under twenty lines. Make exactly one improvement per turn and
state in one sentence what you changed.
"/>
			</CreateActor>
			<CreateActor name="Agent" kind="Agent" {ModelStreamer{provider:OpenAi}}>
				<StoreToolset/>
			</CreateActor>
		</div>
	</div>
	<TuiThreadTranscript>
		<div {ThreadView{thread:$thread}}/>
	</TuiThreadTranscript>
</div>
